    "story_number": "title",
    "title": "Plastics in Pittsburgh:<br>Recycling is getting more complicated",
    "author": "Teake Zuidema",
    "photographer": "Teake Zuidema",
    "background": "https://ps-apps-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/recycling_june_2019/tzu.plastic.17.jpg",
    "background_mobile": "https://ps-apps-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/recycling_june_2019/mobile/tzu.plastic.17.jpg",
    "background_opacity": "0, 0, 0, 0.5"
  },
  {
    "slide_type": "image",
    "story_number": "intro",
    "body": "<p style=\"text-align: left !important;\">By 2015, the world had produced 6,300 million metric tons of plastic waste. Of that, the 2017 study notes that only about 9 percent has been recycled.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: left !important;\">More than 90% of the plastic waste has been buried in landfills, burned in incinerators or ended up littering lands, rivers and oceans.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: left !important;\">Researchers from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration have found that it takes from about 10 to 600 years for plastic objects to biodegrade in the environment.</p>"
  },
  {
    "slide_type": "image",
    "story_number": "intro",
    "body": "<p style=\"text-align: left !important;\">Recycling has always been considered a part of the solution to the problem of plastic pollution. But American recycling is facing a crisis since China in January 2018 announced it would sharply limit plastic imports. The move sparks questions about what actually can be recycled and how plastic waste is handled in Allegheny County.</p>"
  },
  {
    "slide_type": "image",
    "story_number": "0",
    "body": "<p style=\"text-align: left !important;\">These bottles and jugs in the dairy section at Giant Eagle Market District on Centre Avenue are still collected by the recyclers in Allegheny County — as long as they aren’t larger than 3 gallons. But their lids and tabs are not.</p>",
    "background": "https://ps-apps-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/recycling_june_2019/tzu.plastic.00.jpg",
    "background_mobile": "https://ps-apps-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/recycling_june_2019/mobile/tzu.plastic.00.jpg"
  },
