    "story_number": 7,
    "body": "<p style=\"text-align: left !important;\">Volunteer Taylor Erickson fishes a piece of polystyrene foam from a garbage patch that is stuck behind a mooring cell in the Monongahela River. She’s riding on the Rachel Carson, a pontoon boat used by Allegheny CleanWays to remove garbage from the river.</p>",
    "background": "https://ps-apps-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/recycling_june_2019/tzu.plastic.07.jpg",
